               <msContents defective="false">
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1" defective="false">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors (erased); the words sälam “salutation” and hale luya in Text I-1a, elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements.&#xD;
&#xD;
Several groups of lines on the incipit page of Texts I-1a, I-1b, I-3b, I-4, I-5 and I-6, alternating with black lines; several groups of lines in the incipit of Text I-2, alternating with black lines; two initial lines in the incipit of Text I-3a; groups of lines on the incipit page of sections of Texts I-1b and I-3a alternating with black lines; two initial lines of the sections of Texts I-1a and I-4 (sometimes alternating with black lines) and its section numbers; first word of each strophe of Text I-5.</rubric>
                     <incipit defective="false">
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit defective="false">
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note anchored="true"/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1" defective="false">
                     <colophon>Fols. 181va-182ra: ተፈጸመት፡ ዘቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ በ፪፻ወ፶፡ ዓመተ ምሕረት፡ &lt;…&gt;በመዋዕሊሆሙ፡ &lt;…&gt; ዘነበረ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ … Several lines of the extensive colophon have been erased. The writing of the Ms. was completed in 250 year of mercy (= 1598 A.D. or 1674 A.D., cp. ChChron 166,167).</colophon>
                  </msItem>
