                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script" part="N">Hand a: fine but somewhat irregular. Hand b, c, d: mediocre.</ab>
                        <seg type="ink" part="N">Black, red (hand a: vivid red and strong red, hand b: strong crimson, hand c: vivid red, hand d: strong red).</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" corresp="PRS00000" instant="false" full="yes"><!--Only the name of the scribe should be here, with appropriate correspondence--></persName>
                        <date instant="false">Hand a: Second half of the 16th cent;  b: first half of the 20th cent.; c: second half of the 18th cent. (?); d: 20th cent.</date>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Texts I-a, I-3b, I-4, I-5, I-6 (quires I, III-XXV). The handwriting appears irregular throughout the Ms. and changes from careful and neat with slender, broadly spaced and right-sloping letters (quires I, XIV-XXIV) to mediocre resulting in an uneven script with irregularly slanted letters (quires III-XIII). Probably the text was written at several stages.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">quire II (Texts I-b, I-2a and I-3a), recent.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">fols. 89r, 92v (two added miracles of Mary). </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic">fols. 144ra-145vb (two added miracles of Mary).</handNote>
